<annotation>
  <id>70</id>
  <text>
    In a light microscope (LM), visible light is passed through the specimen and then through glass lenses. The lenses refract (bend) the light in such a way that the image of the specimen is magnified as it is projected into the eye or into a camera (see Appendix D).
  </text>
